{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-cacicus-uropygialis", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-cacicus-uropygialis", "name": "Scarlet-rumped cacique", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "taxonomy-species-cacicus-uropygialis", "name": "Scarlet-rumped cacique", "latinName": "Cacicus uropygialis", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Scarlet-rumped cacique（Cacicus uropygialis）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Scarlet-rumped cacique。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": 597.8, "y": -25.06, "z": 268.9}, {"id": "bird-scarlet-rumped-cacique-8bfc5eae", "name": "Scarlet-rumped cacique", "englishName": "Scarlet-rumped cacique", "latinName": "Cacicus uropygialis", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "The scarlet-rumped cacique (Cacicus uropygialis) is a passerine bird species in the New World blackbird family Icteridae. This species has sometimes been split into two species: the scarlet-rumped cacique (Cacicus microrhynchus) and the subtropical cacique (Cacicus uropygialis). Taxonomy The scarlet-rumped cacique was formally described in 1843 by the French ornithologist Frédéric de Lafresnaye based on a specimen collected in Colombia. He coined the binomial name Cassicus uropygialis where the specific epithet is from Medieval Latin uropygium meaning \"rump\". The scarlet-rumped cacique is now one of ten species placed in the genus Cacicus that was introduced in 1799 by the French naturalist Bernard Germain de Lacépède. Three subspecies are recognised: C. u. microrhynchus (Sclater, PL & Salvin, O, 1865) – far northeastern Honduras to eastern Panama (except Darién Province) C. u. pacificus Chapman, FM, 1915 – eastern Panama (Darién Province) to western Colombia and western Ecuador (El Oro) C. u. uropygialis Lafresnaye, 1843 – Andes of Colombia to northwestern Venezuela, eastern Ecuador, and southeastern Peru The taxa C. u. pacificus and C. u. microrhynchus are sometimes treated as a separate species with the English name, the scarlet-rumped cacique. The nominate C. u. uropygialis is then known as the subtropical cacique. Description The scarlet-rumped cacique is sexually dimorphic like many Icteridae, though it mainly concerns size in this species. Males are 23 cm (9 in) long and weigh 68 g (2.4 oz), while the female is 20 cm (8 in) long and weighs 53 g (1.9 oz); This cacique is a slim long-winged bird, with a relatively short tail, blue eyes, and a pale yellow pointed bill. It has mainly black plumage, apart from a scarlet patch on the lower back and upper rump. The female is smaller and a duller black than the male, and the juvenile bird has a brownish tone to the plumage and a brownish-orange rump. The song of these birds is a pleasant wheee-whee-whee-whee-wheet, but the Pacific cacique has a descending melancholy wheeo-wheeo-wheeo-wheeo, while C. m. microrynchus in the narrowest sense has a burry pleeo; C. m. pacificus has a sweeter keeo or a shree. Behaviour Unlike some other caciques they are not usually colonial breeders; like them they have a bag-shaped nest. It is built about 3.5–30 m (11–98 ft) above ground, in a tree which usually also contains an active wasp nest. The bird's nest is 36–64 cm (14–25 in) long, widens at the base, and is suspended from the end of a branch. The normal clutch is two dark-blotched white eggs. The male will assist in feeding the young, but does not incubate. References Further reading Taxonomy of the birds of the world: The complete checklist. p. 524. The Complete Birds of the World: Every Species Illustrated. p. 578.", "shortSummary": "The scarlet-rumped cacique (Cacicus uropygialis) is a passerine bird species in the New World blackbird family Icteridae. This species has…", "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/db/Cacicus_uropygialis_-Panama-8.jpg/960px-Cacicus_uropygialis_-Panama-8.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-cacicus", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-cacicus-uropygialis", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-cacicus", "species": "taxonomy-species-cacicus-uropygialis"}, "expandable": true, "x": 597.8, "y": -25.06, "z": 269.05}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-cacicus", "name": "Cacicus", "latinName": "Cacicus", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Cacicus（Cacicus）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联10种鸟类，如Solitary cacique、Golden-winged cacique、Ecuadorian cacique等10种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 10, "x": -637.95, "y": -93.41, "z": 12.4}], "links": [{"key": "bird-scarlet-rumped-cacique-8bfc5eae__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-cacicus-uropygialis", "source": "bird-scarlet-rumped-cacique-8bfc5eae", "target": "taxonomy-species-cacicus-uropygialis", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-cacicus-uropygialis__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-cacicus", "source": "taxonomy-species-cacicus-uropygialis", "target": "taxonomy-genus-cacicus", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Scarlet-rumped cacique 属于属 Cacicus。"}]}
